nce we killed the Shissar.  I was going to sit out, because they were farther along.  Unfortunately, enough people left that we could not continue the raid.  It was an open raid, thrown together at the last minute, and we did not feel comofortable pulling the temple with 22 people and one cleric.<br>
<br>
If Zambartas stayed after Dreslav and much of the rest of the raid left, he had every right to pull together people and try to take the temple.  Disregarding the fact that he had just spent 5 hours there with the rest of us and going in to take the mob for another enchanter, who was not on the raid at all, is not only incredibly rude, it's an insult to the enchanter community.  We try very much to respect one another, helping each other out, talking about tactics, etc.  I think we're pretty close-knit, and the fact that someone can just walk and and comletely disregard that makes me sick.  You don't care that two of your fellow enchanters just spent 5 hours in Fear listening to that stupid mob shout every few minutes?  Taunting them with one of the hardest pieces?  Fine, go screw off then, and we'll remember what you did to the community if you ever want something from it.  <br>
<br>
And, as was mentioned earlier, if this character was indeed an alt, then fine, don't care about the community you infringed upon.  Be an ass.  I've never been one to disrespect twinks or alts withing my class.  After all, hearing from the perspective of someone who's played another class can sometimes be very interesting and yield lots of info.  The only time I do get sick of twinks or alts is when the players behind them don't give a damn about the community they entered by creating that class and think they're somehow above those who have put a lot of effort into keeping that community close and civil, regardless of guild tag or level.<br>
<br>
I don't know Luulu and I haven't spoken to Zambartas very much, but I respect them as enchanters, and knew when to step aside to let them get their shot at the epic piece.  It was an open raid led by my guild, and I probably could have been an ass and insisted upon a roll if offered.  (Not that we even got that far, obviously, so it really doesn't matter - however, loot rules were announced at the beginning of the raid)  I got tells from several people asking why I was sitting out.  I didn't understand why anyone would even second guess it.  They're farther along, they need it more, they deserve it more.  Simple as that.  It's that kind of respect I'm talking about, and that kind of blatant disregard for courtesy that was shown here.  No, this isn't about guild politics at all.  This is about respect, or rather, lack thereof.<br>
<br>
Not that I speak for all of us, but I'm sure most would agree - on behalf of the enchanters of Lanys, thanks for nothing.</font><P><center><img src = http://members.bellatlantic.net/~mezner/daeonsig2.jpg><br>
